    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have yours of yesterday. Do you mean that you will be allowed to inspect official
                    record and thus be enabled and be at liberty to ascertain and report to your
                    Government whether Waller court was legally constituted and the Waller trial,
                    conviction, and sentence regular and valid according to French law? If so,
                    denial of record would not seem to be absolute, but to have an exception in
                    favor of yourself as ambassador. Please ascertain and report definitely on this
                    point at earliest practicable moment</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
